Job Alert from International Career Employment Weekly

To: Email Alert Subscribers

International Plant Genetic Resources Institute

The International Plant Genetic Resources Institute (IPGRI) is
one of the 15 Future Harvest Centres supported by the
Consultative Group on International Agricultural Research (CGIAR)=2E
IPGRI's strategy is to promote the use of
agrobiodiversity to fight poverty and hunger=2E

Position available:
Legal Specialist in Genetic Resources for Food and Agriculture

The Legal Specialist will advance IPGRI's research and
capacity building agenda concerning laws and policies that
enable the optimum use of genetic resources for food and
agriculture to improve peoples' livelihoods=2E The work will
involve preparation of technical submissions to international
intergovernmental fora, working on projects with national
and subregional partners, and providing technical
assistance concerning genetic resources policy issues to
the Future Harvest Centres of the CGIAR=2E

This position is based at IPGRI's Headquarters near
Rome, Italy=2E

The closing date for applications is 2nd
December 2005 or until the vacancy is filled=2E

Potential appointees should consult the IPGRI website for a
detailed job description, conditions of service and application
details at <a href="http://www=2Eipgri=2Ecgiar=2Eorg">http://www=2Eipgri=2Ecgiar=2Eorg</a>

IPGRI is an equal opportunity employer and strives for staff diversity in
gender and nationality=2E Women and candidates from developing countries
are particularly encouraged to apply=2E

